25namespace internal {
26namespace {
27
28void RemoveOldReports(int64_t now, std::list<CallStats::RttTime>* reports) {
29 static constexpr const int64_t kRttTimeoutMs = 1500;
30 reports->remove_if(
31 [&now](CallStats::RttTime& r) { return now - r.time > kRttTimeoutMs; });
32}
33
34int64_t GetMaxRttMs(const std::list<CallStats::RttTime>& reports) {
35 int64_t max_rtt_ms = -1;
36 for (const CallStats::RttTime& rtt_time : reports)
37 max_rtt_ms = std::max(rtt_time.rtt, max_rtt_ms);
38 return max_rtt_ms;
39}
40
41int64_t GetAvgRttMs(const std::list<CallStats::RttTime>& reports) {
42 RTC_DCHECK(!reports.empty());
43 int64_t sum = 0;
44 for (std::list<CallStats::RttTime>::const_iterator it = reports.begin();
45 it != reports.end(); ++it) {
46 sum += it->rtt;
47 }
48 return sum / reports.size();
49}
50
51int64_t GetNewAvgRttMs(const std::list<CallStats::RttTime>& reports,
52 int64_t prev_avg_rtt) {
53 if (reports.empty())
54 return -1; // Reset (invalid average).
55
56 int64_t cur_rtt_ms = GetAvgRttMs(reports);
57 if (prev_avg_rtt == -1)
58 return cur_rtt_ms; // New initial average value.
59
60 // Weight factor to apply to the average rtt.
61 // We weigh the old average at 70% against the new average (30%).
62 constexpr const float kWeightFactor = 0.3f;
63 return prev_avg_rtt * (1.0f - kWeightFactor) + cur_rtt_ms * kWeightFactor;
64}
65
66} // namespace
67
68constexpr TimeDelta CallStats::kUpdateInterval;
69
70CallStats::CallStats(Clock* clock, TaskQueueBase* task_queue)
71 : clock_(clock),
72 max_rtt_ms_(-1),
73 avg_rtt_ms_(-1),
74 sum_avg_rtt_ms_(0),
75 num_avg_rtt_(0),
76 time_of_first_rtt_ms_(-1),
77 task_queue_(task_queue) {
78 RTC_DCHECK(task_queue_);
79 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
80}
81
82CallStats::~CallStats() {
83 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
84 RTC_DCHECK(observers_.empty());
85
86 repeating_task_.Stop();
87
88 UpdateHistograms();
89}
90
91void CallStats::EnsureStarted() {
92 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
93 repeating_task_ =
94 RepeatingTaskHandle::DelayedStart(task_queue_, kUpdateInterval, [this]() {
95 UpdateAndReport();
96 return kUpdateInterval;
97 });
98}
99
100void CallStats::UpdateAndReport() {
101 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
102
103 RemoveOldReports(clock_->CurrentTime().ms(), &reports_);
104 max_rtt_ms_ = GetMaxRttMs(reports_);
105 avg_rtt_ms_ = GetNewAvgRttMs(reports_, avg_rtt_ms_);
106
107 // If there is a valid rtt, update all observers with the max rtt.
108 if (max_rtt_ms_ >= 0) {
109 RTC_DCHECK_GE(avg_rtt_ms_, 0);
110 for (CallStatsObserver* observer : observers_)
111 observer->OnRttUpdate(avg_rtt_ms_, max_rtt_ms_);
112 // Sum for Histogram of average RTT reported over the entire call.
113 sum_avg_rtt_ms_ += avg_rtt_ms_;
114 ++num_avg_rtt_;
115 }
116}
117
118void CallStats::RegisterStatsObserver(CallStatsObserver* observer) {
119 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
120 if (!absl::c_linear_search(observers_, observer))
121 observers_.push_back(observer);
122}
123
124void CallStats::DeregisterStatsObserver(CallStatsObserver* observer) {
125 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
126 observers_.remove(observer);
127}
128
129int64_t CallStats::LastProcessedRtt() const {
130 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
131 // No need for locking since we're on the construction thread.
132 return avg_rtt_ms_;
133}
134
135void CallStats::OnRttUpdate(int64_t rtt) {
136 // This callback may for some RtpRtcp module instances (video send stream) be
137 // invoked from a separate task queue, in other cases, we should already be
138 // on the correct TQ.
139 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
140 auto update = [this, rtt, now_ms]() {
141 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
142 reports_.push_back(RttTime(rtt, now_ms));
143 if (time_of_first_rtt_ms_ == -1)
144 time_of_first_rtt_ms_ = now_ms;
145 UpdateAndReport();
146 };
147
148 if (task_queue_->IsCurrent()) {
149 update();
150 } else {
151 task_queue_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(task_safety_, std::move(update)));
152 }
153}
154
155void CallStats::UpdateHistograms() {
156 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
157
158 if (time_of_first_rtt_ms_ == -1 || num_avg_rtt_ < 1)
159 return;
160
161 int64_t elapsed_sec =
162 (clock_->TimeInMilliseconds() - time_of_first_rtt_ms_) / 1000;
163 if (elapsed_sec >= metrics::kMinRunTimeInSeconds) {
164 int64_t avg_rtt_ms = (sum_avg_rtt_ms_ + num_avg_rtt_ / 2) / num_avg_rtt_;
165 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_10000(
166 "WebRTC.Video.AverageRoundTripTimeInMilliseconds", avg_rtt_ms);
167 }
168}
